messages.msgSnippet: I m quoting from private e-mail, so don t think you missed something, but... ...
messages.messageBody:
I'm quoting from private e-mail, so don't think you missed something, but...

> So do you consider me booked to the point that I should start telling people
> to go to Houston to hear me if they can't make it to South Carolina? If you
> want me to wait to say anything I will.

<<Yes, you're booked! Go ahead and start spreading the word.>>

So. I want to take NOTHING away from the glorious big conference Kelly is
putting on, which is the seasonal event of the north-American Atlantic coast
this year, but *if* there are people here in the southwest who couldn't
possibly make it to South Carolina in October, you might want to consider a
smaller, quieter conference in Houston.

http://www.angelfire.com/tx/wlr/conference.html

Now featuring me! (And now I get to see some Texas buddies of mine!)

Many of you area aware of this, but although Texas and New Mexico are
touching (for a long long way), Houston is NOwhere near Albuquerque. 850
miles. About as far as Houston to Florida. Seems wrong, but there it is.
So I'll be flying.


Sandra
